<title>Quick Start</title>
<para>Pre-requisites: python3</para>
<para><orderedlist>
<listitem><para>Install <ulink url="https://docs.platformio.org/en/latest/core/installation.html">Platform IO CLI</ulink> <verbatim> python3 -c &quot;$(curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/platformio/platformio/master/scripts/get-platformio.py)&quot;
</verbatim> I haven&apos;t tried this step myself, but if it fails, try to follow the instructions on platform.io&apos;s website. Rob is using platform.io within VS Code. The link for that is <ulink url="https://docs.platformio.org/en/latest/integration/ide/vscode.html#quick-start">here</ulink></para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Clone the repository <verbatim> git clone git@github.com:Safecast/bGeigiezen.git
</verbatim></para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Change branch to Robin dev <verbatim> cd bGeigiezen
 git checkout robin/M5Stack_bGeigieRaku_V2.0
</verbatim></para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Change directory <verbatim> cd bgeigie_firmware_pio
</verbatim></para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Connect the device using USB, compile, and upload <verbatim> pio run -t upload
</verbatim> </para>
</listitem></orderedlist>
</para>
